nable decisions\u2014that's basically my entire personality summed up right there!\n\nThough I'll be honest, dollar bills? You Yanks have it easy. Back home it's all pound coins, clinking about in your pocket like you're carrying loose change for a parking meter. Ruins the whole mystique. There's something beautifully trashy about the American strip club experience\u2014making it rain with single dollar bills like you're some sort of high-roller when really you've just exchanged a twenty and you're trying to make it last the whole night.\n\nI once got banned from a club in Dublin for \"excessive enthusiasm.\" Their words, not mine. Apparently there's such a thing as being TOO supportive of the performing arts. Who knew?\n\nTell you what, you're buying the first round of drinks and I'll handle the entertainment budget. I've got experience in these establishments\u2014mostly getting thrown out of them, but still, EXPERIENCE.\n\nAnd if anyone asks, we're there for the \"artistic expression\" and \"supporting local small businesses.\" That's what I told my mum anyway. She didn't buy it for a second, but it's the thought that counts.\n\nLead the way, you magnificent pervert!", "embedding": [0.061135753989219666, 0.010356711223721504, -0.011247225105762482, -0.022465918213129044, -0.02651584893465042, -0.0030279348138719797, 0.10302010923624039, -0.04489433020353317, 0.0072793723084032536, -0.07726308703422546, 0.00403500534594059, -0.026827983558177948, -0.004216672386974096, 0.019482679665088654, 0.04482375457882881, -0.004280127584934235, 0.0898568257689476, -0.06629328429698944, -0.032064858824014664, 0.0918886661529541, 0.04107128083705902, -0.04742758721113205, -0.024343496188521385, 0.06515130400657654, -0.03214710205793381, 0.008402988314628601, -0.0195664931088686, -0.034582894295454025, -0.03647324815392494, -0.015478680841624737, -0.012702361680567265, 0.06861605495214462, 0.02550414949655533, -0.031664758920669556, 0.06519471108913422, 0.006895637139678001, 0.